00:02:47.760 --> 00:02:51.480
you know, serving on the tables and things.

00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:55.020
In my holidays and every weekend, you know.

00:02:55.020 --> 00:02:56.720
So you travelled to Rhyl from here?

00:02:56.720 --> 00:02:59.480
Yes, you know, and now, when I think of it now,

00:02:59.480 --> 00:03:03.520
at 13, going on a train by yourself,

00:03:03.520 --> 00:03:05.400
you know, and going round the cafes

00:03:05.400 --> 00:03:06.880
and see who wants some staff,

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:10.800
because Rhyl used to be really busy then.

00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:12.600
You know, and they were always taking people on.

00:03:12.600 --> 00:03:14.120
Right.

00:03:14.120 --> 00:03:15.960
And of course, I was brought up in an era

00:03:15.960 --> 00:03:19.480
where you didn't open your wage packet,

00:03:19.480 --> 00:03:23.680
it had to be handed over to your mother unopened.

00:03:23.680 --> 00:03:24.720
And then she'd go through

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:26.840
and give you a little bit of it back.

00:03:27.720 --> 00:03:30.760
You know, it was no like, today you wouldn't do that.

00:03:30.760 --> 00:03:34.760
You know, my two daughters, when they grew up,

00:03:34.760 --> 00:03:37.000
they just gave me some keep, you know,

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.400
something out of their wages.

